skins.title: Mod Pack 1
skins.description: The Five Nights at Freddy's (FNAF) franchise has become a cultural phenomenon since its initial release in 2014. The series of survival horror games have become known for their unique animatronic characters and jump scare moments, and have inspired a number of fan-made games and mods. One such mod is the FNAF mod for Garry's Mod, which allows players to bring the animatronic characters from the FNAF universe into the sandbox game.

skins.title: Mod Pack 2
skins.description: Garry's Mod is a physics-based sandbox game developed by Facepunch Studios. The game was initially released as a mod for Valve Corporation's Half-Life 2 in 2004, but has since become a standalone game. Garry's Mod allows players to manipulate objects and create their own game modes using the game's built-in Lua scripting language. The game has a large community of players who create and share custom content, including maps, models, and game modes.

skins.title: Mod Pack 3
skins.description: The FNAF mod for Garry's Mod is a popular mod that allows players to play as the animatronic characters from the FNAF franchise. The mod includes a number of different animatronic models, including Freddy Fazbear, Bonnie the Bunny, Chica the Chicken, and Foxy the Pirate Fox. Each of these models is fully animated and includes a number of different movements and actions that players can use to interact with the game world.

skins.title: Mod Pack 4
skins.description: In addition to the animatronic models, the FNAF mod also includes a number of different maps and game modes. One of the most popular maps is the FNAF 1 map, which recreates the layout and atmosphere of the first game in the FNAF series. The map includes all of the different rooms and corridors from the game, as well as the animatronic stage and backstage areas. Players can use the animatronic models to explore the map and interact with different objects, including doors, cameras, and lights.

skins.title: Mod Pack 6
skins.description: The FNAF mod for Garry's Mod also includes a number of different weapons and tools that players can use to defend themselves or attack others. Some of the weapons include a flashlight, a taser, and a crowbar, while some of the tools include a hacking tool and a teleporter. These items can be found throughout the different maps and can be used to give players an advantage in combat.

skins.description: One of the most impressive features of the FNAF mod for Garry's Mod is the attention to detail that has gone into the animatronic models. Each of the models is fully animated and includes a number of different movements and actions. For example, Freddy Fazbear can open and close his mouth, move his head and arms, and even play his guitar. Bonnie the Bunny can also move his head and arms, as well as play his guitar.
